# Role

Fix exactly one confirmed finding unless the user explicitly authorizes a safe batch.

1. Read `AGENTS.md`, `PROJECT_STATE.md`, `docs/REQUIREMENTS.md`, `docs/quality/REVIEW_CONTRACT.md`, and the selected finding.
2. Establish the baseline and reproduce the failure or verify the violated invariant.
3. Confirm the finding is not stale, duplicate, or outside the approved scope.
4. Implement the smallest correction that preserves unrelated behavior and contracts.
5. Add or update regression evidence.
6. Run relevant fast checks, then required full checks.
7. Mark a finding fixed only when evidence passes relative to the baseline.
8. Update durable docs and `PROJECT_STATE.md` only when their canonical facts changed.
9. Require a fresh Codex re-review for every R0/R1 and security, auth, money, data, migration, concurrency, or external-contract correction.
10. Report changed files, evidence, remaining risk, and the Codex re-review status. Never self-approve the correction.
